        <h3>How to Perform Prostate Health Checks</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Schedule regular checkups with a healthcare provider after age 40 or earlier if high risk.</li>
          <li>Discuss PSA (Prostate-Specific Antigen) blood tests and digital rectal exams (DRE).</li>
          <li>Maintain a healthy lifestyle including diet and exercise.</li>
          <li>Report any urinary or pelvic symptoms promptly.</li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="article-section">
        <h3>Screening & Early Detection</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Digital rectal examination (DRE)</li>
          <li>Prostate-specific antigen (PSA) blood test</li>
          <li>Regular checkups for men above 40–50, or earlier if high risk</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

